cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.NA, cs.LG, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with the problem of random projections and sparse reconstruction, which are common topics in information theory (cs.IT), data structures (cs.DS), numerical analysis (cs.NA), machine learning (cs.LG), and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of probability in Banach spaces and Gaussian processes also suggests a connection to probability theory and stochastic processes (cs.PR). However, given the focus on linear mapping and pairwise distances, we believe the first five categories are more likely to be relevant.
